summary:
**International Financial Institutions**

* Calls for vigilance in using international financial mechanisms to prevent misappropriation;
* Requests IMF and World Bank to assess Libya's public financial management framework;

**Review of Sanctions**

* Directs Committee to review continuously remaining sanctions on Central Bank of Libya, LAFB, LIA, and LAIP;
* Decides to lift designation of these entities when practical;

**No Fly Zone and Ban on Flights**

* Takes note of improved situation in Libya;
* Intends to review and potentially lift measures imposed by paragraphs 6-12 of resolution 1973 (2011);

**Cooperation and Reporting**

* Requests Secretary-General to report on implementation within 14 days and monthly thereafter;
* Decides to remain actively seized of the matter.
